#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:143
msgid "The meaning of the configure options:"
msgstr "Voici la signification des options de configure&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:146
msgid "<parameter>CONFIG_EFI_STUB</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>CONFIG_EFI_STUB</parameter>"

#. type: Content of:
#. <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:148
msgid ""
"Although the EFI stub is designed to boot a kernel directly from the UEFI "
"firmware (without a bootloader like GRUB), GRUB needs the kernel to be "
"loaded to support the EFI handover protocol enabled by this option."
msgstr ""
"Bien que le bout EFI soit conçu pour démarrer un noyau directement à partir "
"du micrologiciel UEFI (sans un chargeur d'amorçage comme GRUB), GRUB a "
"besoin que le noyau soit chargé pour prendre en charge le protocole de "
"passage de relai autorisé par cette option."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:156
msgid "<parameter>CONFIG_EFI_VARS</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>CONFIG_EFI_VARS</parameter>"

#. type: Content of:
#. <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:158
msgid ""
"Don't use this deprecated option because of a 1024-byte variable size limit."
"  Its function is replaced by <parameter>CONFIG_EFIVAR_FS</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"N'utilisez pas cette option obsolète à cause d'une limite de taille à 1024 "
"octets. Elle est remplacée par <parameter>CONFIG_EFIVAR_FS</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:166
#| msgid ""
#| "<parameter>CONFIG_FB_EFI</parameter> and "
#| "<parameter>CONFIG_FRAMEBUFFER_CONSOLE</parameter>"
msgid ""
"<parameter>CONFIG_SYSFB_SIMPLEFB</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_DRM</parameter>, <parameter>CONFIG_SIMPLEDRM</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_FB</parameter>, and "
"<parameter>CONFIG_FRAMEBUFFER_CONSOLE</parameter>"
msgstr ""
"<parameter>CONFIG_SYSFB_SIMPLEFB</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_DRM</parameter>, <parameter>CONFIG_SIMPLEDRM</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_FB</parameter> et "
"<parameter>CONFIG_FRAMEBUFFER_CONSOLE</parameter>"

#. type: Content of:
#. <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:172
#| msgid ""
#| "The combination of these two options allows the kernel to print debug "
#| "messages (along with Tux logos) at the early stage of the boot process with "
#| "UEFI."
msgid ""
"The combination of these options allows the kernel to print debug messages "
"(along with Tux logos) at the early stage of the boot process with UEFI.  To"
" ensure them functional at the early stage, they shouldn't be built as a "
"kernel module unless an initramfs will be used."
msgstr ""
"La combinaison de ces options permet au noyau d'afficher des messages de "
"débogage (avec les logos de Tux) pendant les premières étapes du processus "
"de démarrage avec UEFI. Pour vous assurer qu'ils seront fonctionnels pendant"
" ces premières étapes, ils ne doivent pas être construits en tant que "
"modules du noyau à moins que vous n'utilisiez un initramfs."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:185
msgid "Find or Create the EFI System Partition"
msgstr "Trouver ou créer la partition EFI système"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:188
msgid ""
"On EFI based system, the bootloaders are installed in a special FAT32 "
"partition called an <emphasis>EFI System Partition</emphasis> (ESP).  If "
"your system supports EFI, and a recent version of Linux distribution or "
"Windows is pre-installed, it's likely that the ESP is already created.  As "
"the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, list all the "
"partitions on your hard drive (replace <userinput>sda</userinput> with the "
"device corresponding to the appropriate hard drive):"
msgstr ""
"Sur les systèmes EFI, les chargeurs d'amorçage sont installés dans une "
"partition FAT32 spéciale appelée <emphasis>partition EFI système</emphasis> "
"(ESP). Si votre système prend EFI en charge, et qu'une version récente de "
"Linux ou Windows est pré-installée, il est probable que l'ESP soit déjà "
"créée. En tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, listez toutes les partitions de votre "
"disque dur (remplacez <userinput>sda</userinput> par le périphérique "
"correspondant au disque dur approprié)&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>fdisk -l /dev/sda</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>fdisk -l /dev/sda</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:201
msgid ""
"The <quote>Type</quote> column of the ESP should be <literal>EFI "
"System</literal>."
msgstr ""
"La colonne <quote>Type</quote> de l'ESP devrait être <literal>EFI "
"System</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:206
msgid ""
"If the system or the hard drive is new, or it's a first time install an UEFI"
" booted OS on the system, the ESP may not exist.  In that case, create a new"
" partition, make a <systemitem class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> file "
"system on it, and set the partition type to <quote>EFI system</quote>.  See "
"the instructions for the emergency boot device above as a reference."
msgstr ""
"Si le système ou le disque dur est neuf, ou si c'est la première "
"installation d'un système UEFI sur le système, l'ESP n'existe peut-être pas."
" Dans ce cas, créez une nouvelle partition, mettez un système de fichier "
"<systemitem class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> dessus et indiquez "
"<quote>EFI system</quote> comme type de partition. Voir les instructions sur"
" le périphérique de démarrage d'urgence plus haut pour référence."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:216
msgid ""
"Some (old) UEFI implementations may demand the ESP to be the first partition"
" on the disk."
msgstr ""
"Certaines (vieilles) implémentations UEFI peuvent demander que l'ESP soit la"
" première partition du disque."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:222
msgid ""
"Now, as the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, create "
"the mount point for the ESP, and mount it (replace "
"<userinput>sda1</userinput> with the device node corresponding to the ESP):"
msgstr ""
"Maintenant, en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, créez le point de montage pour l'ESP "
"et montez-la (remplacez <userinput>sda1</userinput> par le nœud de "
"périphérique correspondant à l'ESP)&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:228
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv /boot/efi &amp;&amp;\n"
"mount -v -t vfat /dev/sda1 /boot/efi</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv /boot/efi &amp;&amp;\n"
"mount -v -t vfat /dev/sda1 /boot/efi</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:232
msgid ""
"Add an entry for the ESP in <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>, so it will be "
"mounted automatically during system boot:"
msgstr ""
"Ajoutez une entrée pour l'ESP dans <filename>/etc/fstab</filename> pour "
"qu'elle soient montée automatiquement au démarrage du système&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:237
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>/dev/sda1 /boot/efi vfat defaults 0 1</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>/dev/sda1 /boot/efi vfat defaults 0 1</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:244
msgid "Mount the EFI Variable File System"
msgstr "Monter le système de fichiers des variables EFI"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:247
msgid ""
"The installation of GRUB on a UEFI platform requires that the EFI Variable "
"file system, <systemitem class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem>, to be "
"mounted.  As the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, "
"mount it if it's not already mounted:"
msgstr ""
"L'installation de GRUB sur une plateforme UEFI demande que le système de "
"fichiers des variables EFI, <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> soit monté. En tant "
"qu'utilisateur <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, montez-le "
"s'il n'est pas encore monté&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:253
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mountpoint /sys/firmware/efi/efivars || mount -v -t efivarfs "
"efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mountpoint /sys/firmware/efi/efivars || mount -v -t efivarfs "
"efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:257
msgid ""
"If the system is booted with UEFI and systemd, <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> will be mounted automatically.  "
"However in the LFS chroot environment it still needs to be mounted manually."
msgstr ""
"Si le système est démarré avec UEFI et systemd, <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> sera monté automatiquement. "
"Cependant dans l'environnement chroot de LFS il faudra toujours le monter "
"manuellement."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:265
msgid ""
"Now add an entry for the <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> in "
"<filename>/etc/fstab</filename> so it will be mounted automatically during "
"system boot:"
msgstr ""
"Maintenant ajoutez une entrée pour <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> dans "
"<filename>/etc/fstab</filename> pour qu'il soit monté automatiquement au "
"démarrage du système&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:271
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars efivarfs defaults 0 0</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars efivarfs defaults 0 0</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:277
msgid ""
"If the system is not booted with UEFI, the directory <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/sys/firmware/efi</filename> will be missing. In this "
"case you should boot the system in UEFI mode with the emergency boot disk "
"created as above."
msgstr ""
"Si le système n'est pas démarré avec UEFI, le répertoire <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/sys/firmware/efi</filename> n'existera pas. Dans ce cas"
" vous devriez démarrer le système en mode UEFI avec le disque de démarrage "
"d'urgence créé plus haut."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:286
msgid "Setting Up the Configuration"
msgstr "Mettre en place la configuration"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:289
msgid ""
"On UEFI based systems, GRUB works by installing an EFI application (a "
"special kind of executable) into <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/efi/EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</filename>, where "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/boot/efi</filename> is the mount point of the"
" ESP, and <literal>[id]</literal> is replaced with an identifier specified "
"in the <command>grub-install</command> command line.  GRUB will create an "
"entry in the EFI variables containing the path "
"<literal>EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</literal> so the EFI firmware can find "
"<filename>grubx64.efi</filename> and load it."
msgstr ""
"Sur les systèmes UEFI, GRUB fonctionne en installant une application EFI (un"
" type d'exécutable spécial) dans <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/efi/EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</filename>, où <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/efi</filename> est le point de montage de l'ESP et"
" <literal>[id]</literal> est remplacé par un identifiant spécifié à la ligne"
" de commande <command>grub-install</command>. GRUB créera une entrée dans "
"les variables EFI contenant le chemin "
"<literal>EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</literal> pour que le micrologiciel puisse "
"trouver <filename>grubx64.efi</filename> et le charger."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:301
msgid ""
"<filename>grubx64.efi</filename> is very lightweight (136 KB with "
"GRUB-2.06~rc1) so it will not use much space in the ESP.  A typical ESP size"
" is 100 MB (for Windows boot manager, which uses about 50 MB in the ESP). "
"Once <filename>grubx64.efi</filename> loaded by the firmware, it will load "
"GRUB modules in the boot partition.  The default location is <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>."
msgstr ""
"<filename>grubx64.efi</filename> est très léger (136 Ko pour GRUB-2.06~rc1) "
"donc il n'utilisera pas de place dans l'ESP. Une taille typique d'ESP est "
"100 Mo (pour le chargeur d'amorçage de Windows, qui prend environ 50 Mo dans"
" l'ESP). Une fois <filename>grubx64.efi</filename> chargé par le "
"micrologiciel, il chargera les modules GRUB dans la partition de démarrage. "
"L'emplacement par défaut est <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:311
msgid ""
"As the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, install the "
"GRUB files into <filename>/boot/efi/EFI/LFS/grubx64.efi</filename> and "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>. Then set up the boot "
"entry in the EFI variables:"
msgstr ""
"En tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, "
"installez les fichiers de GRUB dans "
"<filename>/boot/efi/EFI/LFS/grubx64.efi</filename> et <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>. Ensuite paramétrez l'entrée de "
"démarrage dans les variables EFI&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>grub-install --bootloader-id=LFS --recheck</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>grub-install --bootloader-id=LFS --recheck</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:320
msgid "If the installation is successful, the output should be:"
msgstr ""
"Si l'installation se passe correctement, la sortie devrait être&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:323
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<literal>Installing for x86_64-efi platform.\n"
"Installation finished. No error reported.</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>Installing for x86_64-efi platform.\n"
"Installation finished. No error reported.</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:327
msgid ""
"Issue <command>efibootmgr</command> to recheck the EFI boot configuration.  "
"An example of the output is:"
msgstr ""
"Tapez <command>efibootmgr</command> pour revérifier la configuration de "
"démarrage EFI. Voici un exemple de sortie&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:331
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<literal>BootCurrent: 0000\n"
"Timeout: 1 seconds\n"
"BootOrder: 0005,0000,0002,0001,0003,0004\n"
"Boot0000* ARCH\n"
"Boot0001* UEFI:CD/DVD Drive\n"
"Boot0002* Windows Boot Manager\n"
"Boot0003* UEFI:Removable Device\n"
"Boot0004* UEFI:Network Device\n"
"Boot0005* LFS</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>BootCurrent: 0000\n"
"Timeout: 1 seconds\n"
"BootOrder: 0005,0000,0002,0001,0003,0004\n"
"Boot0000* ARCH\n"
"Boot0001* UEFI:CD/DVD Drive\n"
"Boot0002* Windows Boot Manager\n"
"Boot0003* UEFI:Removable Device\n"
"Boot0004* UEFI:Network Device\n"
"Boot0005* LFS</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:342
msgid ""
"Note that <literal>0005</literal> is the first in the "
"<literal>BootOrder</literal>, and <literal>Boot0005</literal> is "
"<literal>LFS</literal>. This means that on the next boot, the version of "
"GRUB installed by LFS will be used to boot the system."
msgstr ""
"Remarquez que <literal>0005</literal> est en premier dans "
"<literal>BootOrder</literal> et que <literal>Boot0005</literal> est "
"<literal>LFS</literal>. Cela signifie qu'au prochain démarrage, la version "
"de GRUB installée par LFS sera utilisée pour démarrer le système."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:351
msgid "Creating the GRUB Configuration File"
msgstr "Création du fichier de configuration de GRUB"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><indexterm><primary>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:354
msgid "/boot/grub/grub.cfg"
msgstr "/boot/grub/grub.cfg"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:358
msgid ""
"Generate <filename>/boot/grub/grub.cfg</filename> to configure the boot menu"
" of GRUB:"
msgstr ""
"Générez <filename>/boot/grub/grub.cfg</filename> pour configurer le menu de "
"démarrage de GRUB&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:362
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin /boot/grub/grub.cfg\n"
"set default=0\n"
"set timeout=5\n"
"\n"
"insmod part_gpt\n"
"insmod ext2\n"
"set root=(hd0,2)\n"
"\n"
"if loadfont /boot/grub/fonts/unicode.pf2; then\n"
"  set gfxmode=auto\n"
"  insmod all_video\n"
"  terminal_output gfxterm\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"GNU/Linux, Linux 5.10.17-lfs-10.1\"  {\n"
"  linux   /boot/vmlinuz-5.10.17-lfs-10.1 root=/dev/sda2 ro\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Firmware Setup\" {\n"
"  fwsetup\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin /boot/grub/grub.cfg\n"
"set default=0\n"
"set timeout=5\n"
"\n"
"insmod part_gpt\n"
"insmod ext2\n"
"set root=(hd0,2)\n"
"\n"
"if loadfont /boot/grub/fonts/unicode.pf2; then\n"
"  set gfxmode=auto\n"
"  insmod all_video\n"
"  terminal_output gfxterm\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"GNU/Linux, Linux 5.10.17-lfs-10.1\"  {\n"
"  linux   /boot/vmlinuz-5.10.17-lfs-10.1 root=/dev/sda2 ro\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Firmware Setup\" {\n"
"  fwsetup\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:387
msgid ""
"<literal>(hd0,2)</literal>, <literal>sda2</literal>, and "
"<literal>5.10.17-lfs-10.1</literal> should be replaced to match your "
"configuration."
msgstr ""
"Vous devez remplacer <literal>(hd0,2)</literal>, <literal>sda2</literal> et "
"<literal>5.10.17-lfs-10.1</literal> pour correspondre à votre configuration."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:394
msgid ""
"From GRUB's perspective, the files are relative to the partition are used. "
"If you used a separate /boot partition, remove /boot from the above paths "
"(to kernel and to <filename>unicode.pf2</filename>). You will also need to "
"change the set root line to point to the boot partition."
msgstr ""
"Du point de vu de GRUB, les fichiers sont relatifs à la partition utilisée. "
"Si vous utilisez une partition /boot séparée, supprimez /boot dans les "
"chemins précédents (vers le noyau et vers <filename>unicode.pf2</filename>)."
" Vous devrez aussi changer la ligne set root pour pointer vers la partition "
"de démarrage."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:403
msgid ""
"The <literal>Firmware Setup</literal> entry can be used to enter the "
"configuration interface provided by the firmware (sometimes called "
"<quote>BIOS configuration</quote>)."
msgstr ""
"L'entrée <literal>Firmware Setup</literal> peut être utilisée pour entrer "
"dans l'interface de configuration fournie par le micrologiciel (parfois "
"nommée <quote>configuration BIOS</quote>)."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:410
msgid "Dual-booting with Windows"
msgstr "Démarrage double avec Windows"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:413
msgid "Add a menu entry for Windows into <filename>grub.cfg</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Ajoutew une entrée de menu pour Windows dans "
"<filename>grub.cfg</filename>&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:416
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin Windows addition\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Windows 10\" {\n"
"  insmod fat\n"
"  insmod chain\n"
"  set root=(hd0,1)\n"
"  chainloader /EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin Windows addition\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Windows 10\" {\n"
"  insmod fat\n"
"  insmod chain\n"
"  set root=(hd0,1)\n"
"  chainloader /EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:428
msgid ""
"<literal>(hd0,1)</literal> should be replaced with the GRUB designated name "
"for the ESP.  The <literal>chainloader</literal> directive can be used to "
"tell GRUB to run another EFI executable, in this case the Windows Boot "
"Manager. You may put more usable tools in EFI executable format (for "
"example, an EFI shell) into the ESP and create GRUB entries for them."
msgstr ""
"Vous devriez remplacer <literal>(hd0,1)</literal> par le nom désigné par "
"GRUB pour l'ESP. Vous pouvez utiliser la directive "
"<literal>chainloader</literal> pour dire à GRUB de lancer un autre "
"exécutable EFI, dans ce cas le gestionnaire de démarrage de Windows. Vous "
"pouvez ajouter des outils supplémentaires au format exécutable EFI (par "
"exemple un shell EFI) dasn l'ESP et leur créer des entrées GRUB."

